an class=title> Been working on a trilogy about racing...</span><hr size=1> I've been showing it to people at car forums, but I figured I would see what writers would think of it.<br>
<br>
There's a lot of car stuff in this story. I highlight driving talent, and the smart/inexpensive approach to car tuning. Think of a geeky, technically accurate version of &quot;The Fast and The Furious,&quot; that is only about racing, and without the cops and robbers angle. <br>
The entire trilogy makes up a sort of coming-of-age story.<br>
<br>
Here's a quick synopsis of the first part:<br>
<br>
Rev Limit: Rising Star<br>
<br>
Scott wants to join his friend Darren's car club. Darren doesn't want to look like he's playing favorites, so he tells Scott he has to beat him in a race in order to join. Scott has a bit of a problem, since Darren's car is at least twice as powerful as his.<br>
<br>
Scott runs into Shin, a shop owner who sees the potential in him. Shin decides to sponsor Scott, and they begin building up his car. Shin also has Amber, a customer/friend of his, take him out for a driving lesson. To test Scott further, Shin asks Rey, another customer, to ask him to race. <br>
<br>
After racing Rey, Scott gets the news that a guy named Kenneth has been hanging out with Darren and his team. Darren likes Kenneth, and decides that Kenneth and Scott will race to see who will race him for a spot on the team.<br>
<br>
After the race with Kenneth, Rey comes to the shop with Bryan, the leader of his team. Bryan used to be sponsored by Shin, and is jealous that someone else is getting help from him. He wants to race with Scott to see who is the better pupil.<br>
<br>
Finally, Scott squares off with Darren, in a rather anticlimatic race.<br>
<br>
